    "body": "Hey @iamdefinitelyahuman. Thanks for the quick reply. \r\n\r\nI changed the configuration to this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nconsole:\r\n    show_colors: false\r\n ```\r\n\r\nand noticed something super weird. \r\n\r\nIf you see the screenshot below, I type `accounts` three times and nothing happens. Then I deliberately type something which will generate a python exception, and all the `stdout` is flushed at once.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1964\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-05-25 at 10 31 19 PM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8398696/119593968-f0615c80-bda8-11eb-8371-00bd4343d4df.png\">\r\n\r\nNotice that problem is not with brownie specific commands. Regular python commands don't show their outputs either. \r\n\r\n<img width=\"507\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-05-25 at 10 33 29 PM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8398696/119594148-3cac9c80-bda9-11eb-8d6d-f7bcd6ee2e4f.png\">\r\n\r\nIt seems that disabling colors put the console in some sort of buffered mode, and flush doesn't happens at the right time. Pretty weird bug. \r\n",
