    "body": "Ok. the offending code is this:\r\n\r\n```py\r\n        if CONFIG.settings[\"console\"][\"show_colors\"]: \r\n             text = color.highlight(text)\r\n        self.write(text)\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen the colors are enabled, we call `highlight` function from here:\r\nhttps://github.com/eth-brownie/brownie/blob/aaffc21c4445566f66d71deed95b0e8f47391771/brownie/utils/color.py#L186\r\n\r\nIt does an important thing (apart from highlighting the text) of appending a new line character to text. (as observed in this pdb session)\r\n\r\n```py\r\n>>> 4 + 5                                                                                                                    \r\n> ...site-packages/brownie/_cli/console.py(202)_console_write()\r\n    201         import ipdb; ipdb.set_trace()\r\n--> 202         self.write(text)                                      \r\n    203                                                               \r\n\r\nipdb> p text                                                          \r\n'\\x1b[34m9\\x1b[39;49;00m\\n'\r\n```\r\n\r\nHaving a new line causes interpreter to flush, and hence the output. \r\n\r\nI recommend changing the above code to:\r\n\r\n```py\r\ntext = color.highlight(text) if CONFIG.settings[\"console\"][\"show_colors\"] else text + '\\n'\r\n```\r\n\r\nI have verified that everything works nicely after that. \r\n",
